  Description

  FeelingPrepper is a personal mental-wellness journaling app that
  helps you build healthy daily habits using two evidence-based CBT
  (Cognitive Behavioral Therapy) tools. Whether you're managing
  stress, low mood, or just want to stay grounded, FeelingPrepper
  gives you a simple, private space to check in with yourself every
  day.

  WHAT YOU'LL DO

  • GRAPES — Behavioral activation made simple. Log one small
  activity across six categories (Gentle with yourself, Relaxation,
  Accomplishment, Pleasure, Exercise, and Social) to build momentum
  and beat low mood.

  • Cognitive Triangle — Reframe unhelpful thinking. Tap into the
  connection between your Thoughts, Feelings, and Behaviors to
  understand patterns and respond differently.

  • Daily check-ins — A quick, judgment-free space to reflect on how
  you're doing.

  STAY MOTIVATED

  Progress is gamified with a daily streak and a pet companion that
  grows alongside your habits. Small steps, every day, add up.

  PRIVATE BY DESIGN

  Your journal is yours. All entries are your own private content.
  Manage everything from Settings:
  • Export your data anytime as a CSV file
  • Permanently delete your account and all data, right inside the
  app
  • Local-only reminders — no tracking, no ads

  THOUGHTFUL REMINDERS

  Optional local notifications nudge you for daily check-ins,
  streaks, milestones, and your companion — all toggleable in
  Settings. No spam.

  IMPORTANT

  FeelingPrepper is a self-help wellness tool. It is not a medical
  device and is not a substitute for professional care, diagnosis,
  or treatment. If you are in crisis, in-app resources include 988
  (Suicide & Crisis Lifeline), the Crisis Text Line, and 911.

  Start small. Feel prepared.

